{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '540,640p' tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle\"","aggregated_output":"                new JarFile(jarFile).withCloseable { jf ->\n                    jf.entries().each { e ->\n                        def m = (e.name =~ /^META-INF\\/versions\\/(\\d+)\\//)\n                        if (m.find()) {\n                            int v = (m.group(1) as int)\n                            if (v <= runtimeMajor) existingMrJavaVersions.add(v)\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n\n                // Overlay multi-release JAR bytecode in ascending version order. For each META-INF/versions/<v>/ that exists (v ≤ runtime) copy its classes into the output\n                // tree while stripping the MR prefix, so newer versioned classes overwrite older ones and the result matches JVM per-class selection semantics.\n                existingMrJavaVersions.each { int v ->\n                    c.from(zipTree(jarFile)) {\n                        include \"META-INF/versions/${v}/**/*.class\"\n                        eachFile { fcd ->\n                            fcd.path = fcd.path.replaceFirst(\"^META-INF/versions/${v}/\", \"\")\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n                // Ensure later copies overwrite earlier ones\n                c.duplicatesStrategy = DuplicatesStrategy.INCLUDE\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    r.classDirectories.setFrom(files(effectiveDirs))\n    r.additionalClassDirs.setFrom()\n}\n\ngraalvmNative {\n    metadataRepository {\n        enabled = true\n        uri(tck.metadataRoot.get().asFile)\n    }\n    agent {\n    }\n    binaries {\n        test {\n            if (override) {\n                excludeConfig.put(libraryGAV, [\".*\"])\n            }\n            buildArgs.addAll(nativeImageArgs)\n            buildArgs.addAll(nativeTraceBuildArgs)\n            if (generateDynamicAccessReport) {\n                buildArgs.addAll(providers.provider {\n                    DynamicAccessUtils.buildArgsForClasspathEntries(resolveTestedLibraryJars())\n                })\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_35","type":"agent_message","text":"The repo already supports conditional-agent collection, so I’m switching to that workflow for this library. That should give me the metadata actually exercised by the Spock test suite, which is safer than curating a partial reflection list manually."}}
