{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_189","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n '\\\"initialization\\\"|buildTimeInitialization|initialize-at-build-time|runtimeInitialization|build-time' metadata tests src docs -S\"","aggregated_output":"rg: src: No such file or directory (os error 2)\ndocs/architecture.md:17:invariant and its consequences (no build-time-initialization tweaks, no library\ndocs/metadata.md:56:  type (§FS-repository-functional-spec.5.1). No build-time-initialization\ndocs/functional-spec.md:31:Two properties make this achievable: the reachability-metadata schema is itself additive (every entry is gated on `typeReached`), and `native-image` defaults to runtime initialization when no build-time directives are supplied. The hard constraints below preserve that additivity — they are not editorial scope choices but direct consequences of the invariant.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:33:- **No build-time-initialization tweaks.** Metadata bundles must not ship `native-image.properties` or any other directive that moves class `<clinit>` execution into the image builder. Build-time initialization captures state from a non-user environment into the image and breaks additivity. Every library is runtime-initialized by default.\ndocs/functional-spec.md:216:- **Metadata-only bundles.** Metadata files contain only JSON entries described by GraalVM's manual-configuration reference. Native-image properties (`native-image.properties`) and other build-time tweaks are forbidden — by default every library is runtime-initialized.\nmetadata/com.querydsl/querydsl-codegen/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Querydsl Codegen contains the code generation infrastructure used by Querydsl to generate type-safe query classes from annotated domain models and other metadata sources. It provides serializers, naming utilities, and exporter APIs that support Querydsl modules during annotation processing and build-time generation.\",\nmetadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.annotation.bundle/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"org.osgi.annotation.bundle provides OSGi bundle annotations for declaring manifest headers, package exports, requirements, capabilities, attributes, and directives in source code. The annotations are intended for build-time processing and are not used at runtime.\",\ntests/src/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-metadata/4.3.4/src/test/java/io_helidon_common_features/helidon_common_features_metadata/Helidon_common_features_metadataTest.java:61:                .set(\"description\", \"Requires build-time generated metadata\")\ntests/src/io.helidon.common.features/helidon-common-features-metadata/4.3.4/src/test/java/io_helidon_common_features/helidon_common_features_metadata/Helidon_common_features_metadataTest.java:97:                assertThat(aotMetadata.description()).contains(\"Requires build-time generated metadata\");\nmetadata/io.quarkus.gizmo/gizmo2/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Gizmo 2 is a Java bytecode generation convenience library from Quarkus that provides APIs for creating classes, methods, fields, and bytecode-level operations. It is intended for JVM build-time and runtime tooling that needs to emit or transform class files without hand-writing low-level classfile structures.\",\nmetadata/io.quarkus.gizmo/gizmo/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Gizmo is a bytecode generation library for creating and transforming Java classes programmatically. It provides a fluent API over JVM bytecode generation primitives, commonly used by Quarkus extensions and build-time tooling.\",\nmetadata/io.helidon.integrations.graal/helidon-graal-native-image-extension/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Helidon Graal Native Image Extension contributes GraalVM native-image feature registration and configuration for Helidon applications. It scans Helidon, CDI, Jersey, service descriptor, and @Reflected usage at image build time to register required reflection, resources, and build-time initialization.\",\ntests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib/1.7.10/build.gradle:34:            buildArgs.add('--initialize-at-build-time=kotlin.Metadata')\nmetadata/io.undertow/undertow-parser-generator/index.json:26:    \"description\" : \"Undertow Parser Generator is an annotation processor that generates Undertow's HTTP parser classes. It supports build-time parser code generation for the Undertow web server.\",\ntests/src/org.slf4j/jcl-over-slf4j/1.7.0/src/test/java/org_slf4j/jcl_over_slf4j/SimpleLogTest.java:29:            SimpleLog log = new SimpleLog(uniqueLoggerName(\"initialization\"));\ntests/src/org.slf4j/jcl-over-slf4j/1.5.6/src/test/java/org_slf4j/jcl_over_slf4j/SimpleLogTest.java:29:            SimpleLog log = new SimpleLog(uniqueLoggerName(\"initialization\"));\nmetadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-builder/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Quarkus Builder provides the build chain and build step execution APIs used by Quarkus to coordinate extension build-time processing. It models build items, producers, consumers, diagnostics, and execution results so build steps can be ordered and run consistently.\",\ntests/src/com.nimbusds/nimbus-jose-jwt/3.10/src/test/java/com_nimbusds/nimbus_jose_jwt/Nimbus_jose_jwtTest.java:344:                .iv(Base64URL.encode(\"initialization\"))\ntests/src/com.nimbusds/nimbus-jose-jwt/3.10/src/test/java/com_nimbusds/nimbus_jose_jwt/Nimbus_jose_jwtTest.java:353:        assertEquals(\"initialization\", parsedJweHeader.getIV().decodeToString());\n","exit_code":2,"status":"failed"}}
